a:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Rossum is best suited for enterprises, logistics, supply chain, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Salesforce Flow, meanwhile, shines for Salesforce admins, enterprises, sales operations, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2017, Rossum describes itself as \"AI document understanding platform for enterprise data capture.\" Salesforce Flow, established in 1999, positions itself as \"Salesforce's declarative automation engine for complex business processes.\" With 18 years between them, Salesforce Flow brings the maturity and proven track record of a veteran platform, while Rossum offers the fresh perspective and modern architecture of a newer entrant."}]]}]
b:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Rossum** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to overall value and user satisfaction. However, this does not mean Salesforce Flow is a poor choice — far from it. Salesforce Flow excels in its own right, particularly for Salesforce admins and enterprises.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value high accuracy on structured documents, go with Rossum. If extremely powerful for salesforce automation matters more to you, Salesforce Flow is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
